results.name: Expansion of (1+18*x)^(1/3).
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..799
formula: G.f.: (1-18*x)^(1/3) = 1 + 6*x/(G(0)-6*x) where G(k)= k*(1-18*x) + 1+ 6*x + 6*x*(k+1)*(3*k+2)/G(k+1); (continued fraction). - _Sergei N. Gladkovskii_, Jul 06 2012
D-finite with recurrence: n*a(n) +6*(3*n-4)*a(n-1)=0. - _R. J. Mathar_, Jan 20 2020
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jun 22 2005
